caption: Incredible place - very authentic Mexican food (don’t expect a burrito here) and a lovely garden to eat in.  We had the pork shoulder and rib tips, with churro bread pudding for dessert. All outstanding. We’ll definitely be going back. Highly recommend.
Good food decent price Friendly Lady (part owner)  Huge lanai

Fantastic food and lovely server. It’s the real deal Mexican food, authentic with fresh and delicious seafood options. The dessert, which is not on the menu is...holy cow!!  Churro bread pudding.  As good as desserts get.

haven’t even finished my meal and already needed to review - so so so good, and awesome outdoor seating, I almost forgot I was in the city! Feels like a side street in Baja! Super amazing hot sauces and quality meats and veggies!

Pretty unfriendly server, the food was just okay. We spilled the water and apologized and the guy just was visibly angry and cussed under his breath next to me. I guess he can’t just understand that people make mistakes? I hope this business improves.

The only restaurant on Oahu that's truly authentic and traditional Mexican food. From the ingredients to the technique. They make tortillas in house, the beans are frijoles de olla, and there is no shredded cheese in sight. 100% authentic Mexican food does not include shredded cheese, melted cheese, nor hard taco shells. If you want the real deal from the homeland, come here. Their tostadas are FILLING, tacos are delicious (please try the lengua, omg melts in your mouth), the cochinita... The Cochinita. Everything is responsibly priced and it's family owned.

Wow, this is truly authentic homestyle Mexican food.  I've been to Tlaxcalli three times, always for Sunday brunch.  The corn tortillas are homemade, and the best I've ever had.  The chef imports all his spices from Mexico, and the dishes are delicious!  The space is bright and cheerful, and the kitchen is immaculately clean.  This has quickly become one of my favorite restaurants in Honolulu.  A hidden gem in Chinatown, for sure!

Like a lot of people, I went here a month or so ago because it was the only place open at the time, and the food was so good that I had to go back again today.  The campechana is a refreshing seafood dish with fleshy cubes of raw ahi, tender slices of tako, and boiled pieces of shrimp marinading in a tangy tomato-lime sauce with cucumbers and avocados. Delicious on its own, it’s even better with a healthy spoonful of their dark, smoky, vinegar-chili sauce and spooned onto a crunchy fried tortilla chip.  The taquitos? Deep fried crunchy goodness stuffed with shredded meat stewed in spices. It’s served covered in a bed of shredded lettuce and tomatoes, then sprinkled with cheese. It’s good on its own, maybe a 7/10, BUT THEN. Add some hot sauce. Oh god, the hot sauce. They have two types of homemade hot sauce and they are both marvelous. The green sauce is a powerful punch of garlic with a mild dash of spice. Green sauce was my husband’s favorite, even when he was too full to keep eating.  And the red sauce? Ahhhh. Mouth watering heat. Spice lovers will enjoy the kick, but it’s not so hot that you’ll be dying. Ask for some extra water and you’ll be fine. You’ll be better than fine. You’ll be wiggling in your chair in ecstasy, because the combination of red sauce and green sauce and crispy fried Mexican food will be a riot of flavor in your mouth.  The taquitos are an easy 9-9.5/10 with the hot sauces.  Then there’s the chilles rellenos. My favorite, by far. The best version of chilles rellenos I’ve ever had on the island. It’s a large poblano pepper grilled til its tender and perfect, not slimy, not mushy. Just firm enough to help you scoop the flavorful bed of ground beef, spices, and cheese layered and melted on top of it. Soooo good, and so flavorful all by itself. But then you add the red and green sauce to it? Ugh. I could eat this forever. 10/10.  My husband enjoyed the pork shoulder, but with the first three dishes I didn’t have room for another bite. Last time I had it, I remember the meat was really good and the pickled onions had a mild sweetness it comes with warm tortillas, stewed beans, and its own delicious hot sauce.  Overall, this was a great restaurant, incredibly delicious, and worth the drive from Kapolei. Can’t wait to go there again, hopefully sometime soon.

So disappointing  Gas stations make better and cheaper taquitos  Got both the chicken and beef, both had almost no filling, and in both cases just a little bit of beef and chicken, no cheese, no sauce, no seasoning, with just some lettuce dumped on top of them  Dry, plain, ridiculously overpriced, as I said gas station or frozen taquitos better

Favorite new restaurant!  We saw Tlaxacalli after another restaurant nearby was closed.  They opened in October - what a gem!   There are so many things I love about this restaurant - the indoor space is absolutely charming, and the outdoor eating space is epic!  It is beautifully decorated, quiet, inviting.  Best outdoor eating space I've been do on Oahu. This is not your typical Mexican fare.  If you like high quality, truly authentic, masterfully flavorful dishes - eat at Tlaxcalli.  Our party of four chose five different dishes and they were each superb. I ordered the chili relleno.  I am always on the hunt for an excellent chili relleno and almost always disappointed.  This one well exceeded my expectations.  Large, perfectly stuffed pablano chili in a bowl with the most incredible sauce!  loved the white beans in a savory broth. You can choose seafood, beef, mushroom or chicken. The salsa's were so flavorful - I'm still craving them days later. Excellent service by sweet owner.  Please support this locally owned, family business. I hope they make it through the pandemic. We need to support local small businesses!
Unlike more typical Mexican restaurants, Julio offers regional dishes. The braised oxtail and the ceviche were both excellent. We will gladly come back again.

What an incredible little restaurant!  This was my first time eating here, and I immediately noticed how clean the kitchen and dining area were- it’s such a great space!  The food was amazing and the service was excellent. I’m so impressed with Tlaxcalli and cannot wait to eat there again soon!
Wow - I'm impressed! Delicious, well-crafted Mexican food in a clean and beautiful space. I'm already looking forward to another visit!
Fantastic food and outdoor setting.  Recommend the Ceviche, chilie rellenos, and tacos

So clean and I like the decorations here. Julio is extremely friendly and personable! Ordering 1 of each taco for lunch. Sign in your info in front with large hand sanitizer . Help yourself to sanitizer a plus.  Facility includes his and hers restrooms. Will be updating food reviews soon.5 stars!

Absolutely the most amazing service. The food was to die for. + Price is very reasonable.  I ordered take out, and enjoyed the meal tremendously. That being said, I am SO SO SO excited to have this restaurant near me. I truly loved the tacos and the ceviche, (both poke and shrimp were divine). Cant wait to try more dishes next.  Plus their hot sauces are soooo yammy!!!
Ordered take out.  Their rib-tips dish was just bones and gristle boiled in hot sauce.  Ended up having to throw away inedible garbage and find something else to eat.

Went there carrying food from another restaurant(left overs)that we went sampling. Not the slightest intention of eating it there by no means. But the server quickly asked if we have food in our container. We said yes and thought nothing about it. The server then told us that no outside food was allowed, even though at no point we were going to even open the container in its presence. But he was just rude, seemed annoyed to point at the menu. Tge k side looks nothing of what I would think mexican but k cant talk about the food since, got no chance to try it.
Very impressed. The chef cooked just for us. We were the only ones there so it felt private and fancy. The flavors were fresh with a nostalgic taste of home.
This is authentic mexican food! I can't recommend this restaurant enough. If you are in Hawaii and are craving authentic mexican food, this is it.

It was pleasant discovery to dine here. The menu was very different than what you’ll find on a “typical” Mexican restaurant menu. And everything we tried was really good! I loved the chipotle ahi caesar, horchata was made with coconut milk and tasted light and comforting with a hint of cinnamon and sweetness. The mushroom chile relleno was a veggie lover’s delight for both the amount of veggies and the flavor. Impress your friends and take them here!

Wow! So glad we walked into this new & unique Mexican restaurant. Very friendly owner who opened when other places are closing. Tasty non-creamy Caesar salad, with a light dressing & a massive hunk of ahi! My mom got the chili realano which wasn't fried, so much lighter than expected, but stuffed with mushrooms & cheese. Yum!
